[00:00:00]Lesson 30 Exploring the sea-floor\n
[au:]海底勘探\n
[00:05.16]First listen and then answer the following question.\n
[au:]听录音,然后回答以下问题.\n
[00:09.20]How did people probably imagine the sea-floor before it was investigated?\n
[au:]在开展海底研究前,人们想象中的海底是什么样的?\n
[00:16.23]Our knowledge of the oceans a hundred years ago\n
[au:]100年前,我们关于海洋的认识\n
[00:21.78]was confined to the 2-dimensional shape of the sea surface\n
[au:]仅限于知道海面是二维平面形的,\n
[00:26.35]and the hazards of navigation presented by the irregularities in depth\n
[au:]以及浅水区的深浅不一给航行带来的危险性,\n
[00:31.30]of the shallow water close to the land.\n
[au:]即靠边近陆地的浅水区.\n
[00:34.20]The open sea was deep and mysterious,\n
[au:]无边无际的海洋深邃而又神秘,\n
[00:38.73]and anyone who gave more than a passing thought to the bottom confines of the oceans\n
[au:]凡是稍稍想过大海海底的人\n
[00:44.19]probably assumed that the sea bed was flat.\n
[au:]大概都会认为海底是平坦的.\n
[00:48.04]Sir James Clark Ross had obtained a sounding of over 2,400 fathoms in 1839,\n
[au:]1839年,詹姆斯.克拉克.罗斯爵士曾测得海水深度超过2,400英寻;\n
[00:56.34]but it was not until 1869,\n
[au:]但直到1869年,\n
[00:59.34]when H.M.S.Porcupine was put at the disposal of the Royal Society for several cruises\n
[au:]皇家学会用英国"豪猪"号舰艇进行了几次巡航后,\n
[01:06.26]that a series of deep soundings was obtained in the Atlantic\n
[au:]才在大西洋测得一个个海水深度,\n
[01:11.49]and the first samples were collected by dredging the bottom.\n
[au:]同时通过挖掘海底,取得了研究海底的首批样品.\n
[01:15.57]Shortly after this the famous H.M.S. Challenger expedition\n
[au:]此后不久,英国著名的 "挑战者"号舰艇对海底的那次考察,\n
[01:20.62]established the study of the sea-floor\n
[au:]把对海床的研究确立为\n
