[au:]一个值得一流物理学家和地质学家从事的研究课题.\n
[01:28.30]A burst of activity associated with the laying of submarine cables\n
[au:]铺设海底电缆的热潮\n
[01:33.62]soon confirmed the Challenger's observation\n
[au:]很快证实了"挑战者"号的观察结果:\n
[01:36.45]that many parts of the ocean were two to three miles deep,\n
[au:]海洋中很多地方可深达两三英里,\n
[01:40.81]and the existence of underwater features of considerable magnitude.\n
[au:]水下特征差异极大.\n
[01:45.92]Today,enough soundings are available to enable a relief map of the Atlantic to be drawn\n
[au:]现在已有足够的水深测量数据来绘制一张大西洋洋底地形图,\n
[01:52.95]and we know something of the great variety of the sea bed's topography.\n
[au:]而且我们对海底地形的千变万化也有了一定的了解.\n
[01:58.01]Since the sea covers the greater part of the earth's surface,\n
[au:]既然海洋覆盖着地球的大部分表面,\n
[02:02.27]it is quite reasonable to regard the sea floor\n
[au:]因此完全有理由把海床\n
[02:05.35]as the basic form of the crust of the earth\n
[au:]看作地壳的基本模壳,\n
[02:08.55]with,superimposed upon it,the continents,\n
[au:]上面附加着大陆\n
[02:12.33]together with the islands and other features of the oceans.\n
[au:]以及岛屿和海洋的其他形态.\n
[02:15.85]The continents form rugged tablelands\n
[au:]大陆是崎岖不平的高地,\n
[02:19.87]which stand nearly three miles above the floor of the open ocean.\n
[au:]高出辽阔海洋海底近三英里.\n
[02:24.41]From the shore line,\n
[au:]从海岸线\n
